President Donald Trump issued a proclamation on November 17, 2017, during National Family Week, emphasizing the importance of preserving and promoting strong families. The proclamation recognizes the diversity of families and highlights their role as the fundamental unit of society. It calls for individuals to work every day to nurture the bonds of love and loyalty within their families. The proclamation also emphasizes the need for federal policies that support families, such as tax policies that allow Americans to dedicate more resources to providing for their families. It also mentions the need to address the opioid crisis, which has devastated many American families and communities. The proclamation concludes by urging communities, churches, and individuals to observe National Family Week with appropriate ceremonies and activities.